ra Kinsale, Flowers from the Storm\n|\nMark to yourself the gradual way in which you have been prepared for, and are now led by an irresistible necessity to enter upon your great labour.\n\n- William Makepeace Thackeray, The Book of Snobs\n|\nWhen you invite people to share in your miracle, you create future allies during rough weather.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nYou see, that is the sad, sorry, terrible thing about sarcasm.It's really funny.\n\n- Brandon Sanderson, Alcatraz Versus the Evil Librarians\n|\nBe not anxious;yesterday is your experience, today is your experiment and tomorrow is your expectation. Maximize the time!\n\n- Ifeanyi\n|\nHow is there laughter, how is there joy, as this world is always burning?\n\n- Jack Kerouac, Some of the Dharma\n|\nI'm learning English at the moment. I can say 'Big Ben', 'Hello Rodney', 'Tower Bridge' and 'Loo'.\n\n- Cher\n|\nYou are the sun, and I'm the moon. In your shadow I can shine.\n\n- Tokio\n|\nYou didn’t understand the poem, but that was because it wasn’t for you. It was for me to understand the pain you put me through.\n\n- Dominic\n|\nStudies have shown that, at least among students, popularity equals visibility.\n\n- Alexandra Robbins, The Geeks Shall Inherit the Earth: Popularity, Quirk Theory and Why Outsiders Thrive After High School\n|\nremembering is a great invention of the mind, and if you try hard enough you can remember anything, whether it really happened or not.\n\n- Rodman Philbrick, Freak the Mighty\n|\nSometimes, we can’t help but to shed tears!\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nReality was dawning on him and he hated reality. If you were him, so would you.\n\n- Carla H. Krueger, The Social Worker\n|\n...Being a mother is like being a gardener of souls. You tend your children, make sure the light always touches them; you nourish them. You sow your seeds, and reap what you sow.\n\n- Karen   White, Sea Change\n|\nMake no mistake, every child has his own light, no matter how difficult or defiant or unlikeable he or she might seem.\n\n- Nancy Rose, Raise the Child You've Got—Not the One You Want\n|\nFor me the thing that signals a great story is what we might call its autonomy, the fact that it detaches itself from its author like a soap bubble blown from a clay pipe.\n\n- Julio Cortázar, Around the Day in Eighty Worlds\n|\nJust as we shine the light of scrutiny on those around us, so must we also use it to illuminate our own lives\n\n- Shane Eric Mathias, The Happiness Tree: Grow Your Happiness by Cultivating a Healthy, Creative and Purposeful Life\n|\nI had evolved a year too soon, and it nearly broke me\n\n- Carlyle Labuschagne, The Broken Destiny\n|\nThe body is a temple, where God dwells.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nSometimes it's the toughest moments that you learn the most about yourself, and the more you know yourself, the less you are willing to give away.\n\n- Jennifer Love Hewitt, The Day I Shot Cupid: Hello, My Name Is Jennifer Love Hewitt and I'm a Love-aholic\n|\nWe are created for the sake of love. When we experience love in family life, it is heavenly, but it is still only an image of the greater glory we hope to behold in heaven.\n\n- Scott\n|\nA credit card allows you transcend time. For it allows you to put off until tomorrow what you bought today, while you are still paying off what you bought yesterday.\n\n- Robert\n|\nIntent matters. Integrity matters. Courage matters. If you have the three, nothing else matters\n\n- Sharad\n|\nWith self-courage, self-confidence and self-will, you will master the act.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThe better you were able to imagine what you wanted to imagine, the farther you could flee from reality.\n\n- Haruki Murakami, The Wind-Up Bird Chronicle\n|\nDemocracy is the process to elect the Government of the Upper class or caste people, by the poor people and for the corporate people - Idiotneil\n\n- Neil\n|\nThere is humor in the darkest of moments - People who I have loved and passed away, and very high stake situations where you can't help but laugh. I think that's very human.\n\n- Rose\n|\nJoel Cairo: You always have a very smooth explanation ready.Sam Spade: What do you want me to do, learn to stutter?\n\n- Dashiell Hammett, The Maltese Falcon\n|\nLove anyone and everyone, don't fear for rejection. Love is an inner perception, there is only love, no place for rejection.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen you try hard to get something, but you gain nothing, this is what's called depression.\n\n- Al-Hanouf\n|\nThey were new money, without a doubt: so new it shrieked. Their clothes looked as it they'd covered themselves in glue, then rolled around in hundred-dollar bills.\n\n- Margaret Atwood, The Blind Assassin\n|\nA clear prayer for which you take sole responsibility has no option but to manifest, if not today or tomorrow, then the day after that.\n\n- Pooja\n|\nNo matter how you define success, you will need to be resilient, empowered, authentic, and limber to get there.\n\n- Joanie Connell, Flying Without a Helicopter: How to Prepare Young People for Work and Life\n|\nToday's society is wanting in such a way that Honor, Integrity, Trust, Compassion, Empathy are left for the homeless and their pets.\n\n- Solange\n|\nLook at the rain long enough, with no thoughts in your head, and you gradually feel your body falling loose, shaking free of the world of reality. Rain has the power to hypnotize.\n\n- Haruki Murakami, South of the Border, West of the Sun\n|\nGarfield's assassination attempt made 'the whole nation care'.\n\n- Jefferson\n|\nBeing a Hot Mom means being respected as a mom and a woman. And, the key to being a Hot Mom is having a sense of humor about yourself and all the crazy situations that arise.\n\n- Jami\n|\nLoneliness was a full-body sensation, an anti-exhilaration, from his core outward.\n\n- Charlie Jane Anders, All the Birds in the Sky\n|\nPositive thinking is great, if you'll take action.\n\n- Guy\n|\nSometimes doing the right thing does take more courage, but the feeling it gives you deep inside makes it worth it.\n\n- V.C. Andrews, Pearl in the Mist\n|\nIt Begins with skepticism. The history of human folly, and our own susceptibility to illusions and fallacies, tell us that men and women are fallible.\n\n- Steven Pinker, The Better Angels of Our Nature: Why Violence Has Declined\n|\nOnce you discover that failure is survivable, your fear of it subsides. Failure is not opposite to success, just part of its process.\n\n- T\n|\nYou have to believe what you're saying if you're going to convince me. I just can't break that rule, even if I want to.\n\n- Ashly\n|\nI fell in love with you like the stars fell in love with the sky, without you I am empty and bare.\n\n- Seja\n|\nIt is the roof that fights the rain, but the builder who gets all the glory.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nMen are men, unfortunately, no matter what their shape, and inclined to sin.\n\n- Ray Bradbury, The Martian Chronicles\n|\nMarriage is a great blessing, but it can be a great lesson\n\n- Ernest"